WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:22.640 --> 00:24.551
Adam and Rachel,

00:24.640 --> 00:28.599
here follows a wedding video diary
of your special day.

00:29.640 --> 00:31.437
Watch and enj...

00:37.160 --> 00:39.310
Righty-o. Ready when you are.

00:39.400 --> 00:42.790
Oooh, hang on a minute. Olivia's just
been sick.

00:46.960 --> 00:47.915
<i>And...action!</i>

00:48.000 --> 00:49.911
Put the gun down, will you?

00:50.000 --> 00:53.788
Josh, you're being really tiresome.
Put the gun down.

00:53.880 --> 00:55.791
<i>Put the gun down!</i>

01:02.120 --> 01:05.271
Couple of minutes, Pete. Couple of minutes.

01:07.320 --> 01:09.231
<i>Ready? Go.</i>

01:09.320 --> 01:12.437
Adam and Rachel, this will give
you some idea

01:12.520 --> 01:14.750
of what family life will be like.

01:14.840 --> 01:17.195
Except, of course, they can't have children.

01:18.800 --> 01:20.518
Er, sorry, can we rewind?

01:25.800 --> 01:27.870
I don't know about this, Pete.

01:27.960 --> 01:30.110
Come on, everybody's doing it.

01:30.200 --> 01:32.156
Right. Recording.

01:32.600 --> 01:34.556
Go.

01:35.200 --> 01:37.953
I got the number for the divorce lawyer.

01:38.040 --> 01:42.079
Oh, no!
Look, a message for the newlyweds. Yes?

01:43.120 --> 01:45.031
All right.

01:45.120 --> 01:47.076
<i>And go.</i>

01:50.000 --> 01:51.956
Really good luck.

01:56.600 --> 01:58.556
Will that do?

02:00.560 --> 02:02.516
<i>Oh, forget it!</i>

02:03.640 --> 02:05.153
I can never sleep when I'm excited.

02:05.240 --> 02:09.199
You should do what I do. - Didn't work.
I've never been married before.

02:10.039 --> 02:12.110
There is one nagging concern.

02:12.200 --> 02:15.351
Oh, yeah? What's that?
- Are you recording this?

02:15.440 --> 02:17.351
I'm doing the whole day.

02:17.440 --> 02:20.352
Forget it!
- Hang on. I'll be discreet.

02:20.560 --> 02:23.154
Which is spelt...
- Two Es and a T.

02:23.240 --> 02:25.674
Dating a teacher's doing you good.

02:25.760 --> 02:28.558
OK, my one nagging concern is this.

02:29.600 --> 02:33.593
Your wedding day is meant to be the
happiest day of your life - or one of them.

02:33.680 --> 02:35.989
What if it's not? What if
you're at the altar

02:36.080 --> 02:38.674
and you think, ''I could be
happier than this''?

02:38.760 --> 02:40.671
Won't happen.

02:40.760 --> 02:43.513
You're not getting married in a church.

02:43.600 --> 02:45.556
Why shouldn't it be happy?

02:45.640 --> 02:47.835
How did you feel on your wedding day?

02:48.920 --> 02:50.148
Hung over.

02:50.240 --> 02:52.595
Oh, yeah. Sorry.

02:52.680 --> 02:55.752
Apart from that, you know, happy.

02:57.320 --> 02:59.231
Ecstatically happy.

02:59.320 --> 03:03.074
Hey, no tears.
If you start blubbing, I'm gonna have to.

03:03.160 --> 03:05.116
I'm sorry.

03:05.600 --> 03:08.160
I just don't want it to be a let-down.

03:11.320 --> 03:13.356
Are you having that sausage?

03:13.880 --> 03:15.791
You'll have a lovely time.

03:15.880 --> 03:18.075
Rach, the caterers are here.

03:18.160 --> 03:20.071
<i>That's the good news.</i>

03:20.160 --> 03:22.754
Jenny's still not here. Oi!

03:22.840 --> 03:24.592
Isn't it a bit early to be doing that?

03:24.680 --> 03:26.830
Yes! Oh, Karen, come here.

03:26.920 --> 03:29.559
Come and tell me something

03:29.640 --> 03:31.596
to take my mind off things.

03:32.800 --> 03:36.475
Do you think it's at all possible
that David might be having an affair?

03:37.360 --> 03:40.636
David's about as likely to have an affair
as the Pope.

03:40.720 --> 03:44.713
Women do find him attractive, you know.
David, I mean.

03:44.800 --> 03:46.711
David?

03:46.800 --> 03:50.554
No! No. He's absolutely devoted
to you and the children.

03:52.320 --> 03:55.392
No, David is...a husband and a father.

03:55.480 --> 03:57.198
He's not a...
- Man?

03:57.280 --> 03:59.236
..adulterer.

04:02.720 --> 04:04.711
Why, do you think he might be?

04:04.800 --> 04:08.315
Oh, I don't know. I'm probably
being ridiculous.

04:08.400 --> 04:10.356
Yeah, you are.

04:10.440 --> 04:13.796
Thanks, though. For a moment there
you did actually take my mind off it.

04:13.880 --> 04:15.199
Good.

04:15.280 --> 04:17.430
<i>Adam, love, what are you doing?</i>

04:17.519 --> 04:20.875
Oh, come on! That's Mummy's lipsticks.

04:24.240 --> 04:26.151
You look like a clown.

04:26.240 --> 04:30.392
Come on. Listen, go and get some toys
to take to your nan's.

04:30.480 --> 04:33.233
Not your Darth Maul mask. It scares her.

04:33.320 --> 04:37.598
All right, I'm coming! I'm coming.
I'm coming.

04:39.840 --> 04:41.319
Oh, it's you.

04:41.400 --> 04:44.278
Just picking up some stuff. Hiya, tiger.

04:46.160 --> 04:48.071
Go on. Go and get your toys.

04:50.160 --> 04:51.309
I'm bringing these back.

04:51.400 --> 04:53.914
Great. Saves me changing the locks.

04:54.000 --> 04:57.356
Weren't you coming when we were out?
- You're supposed to be out.

04:57.440 --> 05:00.159
Help yourself. Don't steal anything.

05:05.800 --> 05:08.030
Oh! God, doesn't time drag?

05:09.080 --> 05:12.675
What? Waiting for your wedding?
- It's like waiting to take a driving test.

05:12.760 --> 05:14.512
I failed mine first time.

05:15.680 --> 05:17.591
Driving test.

05:17.680 --> 05:20.717
Think you'll ever do it again?
- What? My driving test?

05:20.800 --> 05:21.835
No.

05:21.920 --> 05:23.990
Well, we're not divorced yet.

05:24.080 --> 05:25.559
I can't see it happening again.

05:26.600 --> 05:28.079
What about Emma?

05:29.120 --> 05:30.872
Emma?

05:31.920 --> 05:33.558
Wow, this looks delicious!

05:33.640 --> 05:36.074
It's thrown together. I had
detention after school.

05:36.160 --> 05:38.310
Oh, aye? What have you been up to?

05:38.400 --> 05:40.595
No, I was taking it. Oh...I see.

05:42.000 --> 05:44.673
Emma's just been made head of careers.

05:44.760 --> 05:46.671
Maybe she can get you one!

05:46.760 --> 05:48.671
<i>She's a lovely girl.</i>

05:48.760 --> 05:51.672
Who's got the garlic bread?
- Who do you think?

05:51.760 --> 05:54.672
Oh, fatty fathead!
- Oh! Cheeky monkey!

05:54.760 --> 05:59.038
Look, anchovies! I don't want anchovies.
- Oh, I'll have them.

05:59.120 --> 06:01.554
Oh, no! No, no, I'm not kissing you.

06:01.640 --> 06:03.756
Especially not with tongues.

06:05.360 --> 06:07.191
She's a lovely girl.
- Jenny?

06:07.280 --> 06:08.713
Emma.

06:08.800 --> 06:10.711
Yeah, Emma.

06:10.800 --> 06:13.473
That reminds me. I must give her a call.

06:13.560 --> 06:15.471
Aw, that's sweet.

06:15.560 --> 06:19.235
Right, first drink of the day.
Amaretto or Schnapps?

06:19.320 --> 06:21.276
Schnapps!

06:29.360 --> 06:31.715
Right, well, that's everything.

06:33.200 --> 06:35.156
Bob.com logging off.

06:36.200 --> 06:38.111
Going somewhere?

06:38.200 --> 06:43.991
Yeah, for the 79th time,
Adam and Rachel's wedding. I told you.

06:44.080 --> 06:46.275
Oh, yeah. Sorry about that.

06:46.360 --> 06:47.554
What are you sorry about?

06:47.640 --> 06:49.710
Rachel. She deserves better.

06:49.800 --> 06:52.553
Than Adam?
How the hell would you know?

06:52.640 --> 06:55.154
The fact that they made me unwelcome

06:55.240 --> 06:58.391
had nothing to do with why
we didn't work out?

06:59.520 --> 07:03.115
No, no. I think that's just a
convenient excuse.

07:03.200 --> 07:07.716
You won't have a word said against them.
- What's to say? My friends are reliable.

07:07.800 --> 07:11.759
Look it up in a dictionary. First sign of
trouble, you won't see them sneaking out!

07:11.840 --> 07:15.594
You know nothing about your friends!
- I know...

07:15.680 --> 07:18.672
I know they're worth more than you are,
Mr Millionaire.

07:18.760 --> 07:20.910
Yeah, right.
- They're not hypocrites.

07:21.000 --> 07:22.513
Who needs a dictionary now?

07:22.600 --> 07:23.874
Shut up.

07:23.960 --> 07:25.951
You don't know what it means.
- Whatever!

07:26.040 --> 07:29.589
Oh, yeah? Ask David, Mr Family Man,
cheating on his wife!

07:29.680 --> 07:32.069
What are you talking about?

07:34.440 --> 07:36.670
We would never have fitted
our wedding in here.

07:36.760 --> 07:38.432
Yeah, 300 of our closest friends.

07:38.520 --> 07:40.954
Most of whom we haven't seen since.

07:41.040 --> 07:43.508
Can I have a box from the kitchen?
- I'll go.

07:44.560 --> 07:46.676
We appreciate this so much.

07:46.760 --> 07:50.275
We're just so happy
you two are finally getting it together.

07:50.360 --> 07:52.510
You recommend marriage, then?

07:52.600 --> 07:54.511
Absolutely.

07:54.600 --> 07:56.556
David, thank you!

07:59.440 --> 08:03.513
You'll never guess what Karen
told me earlier. - What?

08:03.600 --> 08:07.309
Rachel, your father's here.
He says he wants a word.

08:07.400 --> 08:09.356
OK.

08:16.520 --> 08:19.717
I didn't expect to see you until
the registry office.

08:19.800 --> 08:22.109
We wouldn't have a chance to talk.

08:22.200 --> 08:25.476
Why don't you go upstairs?
It's private there.

08:25.560 --> 08:27.516
No, here's fine.

08:30.600 --> 08:34.115
Your mum sends her love.
She can't wait to see you.

08:34.200 --> 08:36.155
I can't wait to see her.

08:37.960 --> 08:41.669
We're disappointed it's not in church,
but that's your decision.

08:42.799 --> 08:45.030
Is that what you came here to say?

08:45.120 --> 08:47.111
We've had our differences,

08:47.200 --> 08:50.556
but all said and done, you're still
my daughter.

08:50.640 --> 08:53.393
The eldest and the first to get married.

08:53.480 --> 08:55.436
I'd like to give you away.

08:57.280 --> 08:59.475
I wanted Mum to be here today.

08:59.560 --> 09:01.471
That's why you're invited.

09:01.560 --> 09:03.516
And that's the only reason.

09:04.560 --> 09:07.950
David? You've agreed to give me away,
haven't you?

09:09.080 --> 09:11.036
I'm sorry?

09:12.280 --> 09:14.236
How long now?

09:15.440 --> 09:16.350
45 minutes.

09:19.440 --> 09:21.351
Pfff! What?!

09:21.440 --> 09:23.351
W-What? Why didn't you say?

09:23.440 --> 09:26.193
We're not dressed. The car will be here.

09:26.280 --> 09:28.236
Till Grandstand.

09:30.840 --> 09:34.833
Yeah, and we've got enough time
for all of Football Focus

09:34.920 --> 09:36.876
and half a horse race.

09:38.760 --> 09:40.671
Can I ask you something?

09:40.760 --> 09:42.751
Mm-hm.
- In your capacity as best man.

09:42.840 --> 09:45.513
If it's about the speech, don't worry.

09:45.600 --> 09:48.990
No, say what you want.
It's about masturbation.

09:51.080 --> 09:54.675
When you were with Jenny,
you stll used to wank, yeah?

09:54.760 --> 09:56.990
Of course I did. Don't you?

09:57.080 --> 10:00.959
Yeah, well, all men do.
And anyway, I'm Presbyterian.

10:01.040 --> 10:02.109
Did Jenny?

10:02.200 --> 10:05.192
What? Go walkabout in the bush down under?

10:07.240 --> 10:09.754
Well, I'm sure she did before we met.

10:09.840 --> 10:11.956
But after that um...

10:12.040 --> 10:14.998
You're worried about Rachel, aren't you?

10:15.080 --> 10:17.674
You're worried you're not pushing
the right buttons.

10:17.760 --> 10:19.478
Don't be ridiculous. No.

10:19.560 --> 10:21.471
It's just the other day...

10:29.120 --> 10:30.235
I don't mind.

10:30.320 --> 10:32.311
It just seems odd, doesn't it?

10:32.400 --> 10:35.915
When I'm in the house,
just before we get married.

10:37.560 --> 10:42.714
You didn't confront her about it, did you?
- What? Ask her? Er... ha, ha!

10:44.080 --> 10:46.435
It's a difficult one, this. Yeah.

10:48.160 --> 10:50.116
I feel the need to know.

10:52.360 --> 10:54.999
I can always ask Jenny, if you like.

10:55.080 --> 10:58.789
What, if Rachel goes walkabout
in the bush down under?

11:04.720 --> 11:08.110
Well, OK. But remember how to
spell ''discreet''.

11:08.600 --> 11:11.990
Rachel's put me in a very difficult position.
- Well, what did you say?

11:12.080 --> 11:14.958
What could I say? Yes.
- What, in front of her father?

11:15.040 --> 11:16.996
Clearly she wanted me to.

11:17.760 --> 11:21.070
What went on between them anyway?
- Oh, David, he's not a very nice man.

11:22.120 --> 11:24.554
He's a bigot and a drinker.

11:24.640 --> 11:27.552
Oh, yeah?
- No, not like my mother.

11:27.640 --> 11:30.154
Quite seriously. He used to hit
Rachel's mum.

11:31.360 --> 11:32.918
God, to think I shook his hand.

11:33.000 --> 11:37.357
So I wouldn't feel too badly
about taking his place, darling.

11:39.960 --> 11:42.872
Jenny.
- Hi, Karen.

11:42.960 --> 11:45.474
Hi, Jenny.
- David.

11:45.560 --> 11:46.959
Hello!

11:48.880 --> 11:51.952
Come on! The car'll be here in five minutes.

11:54.120 --> 11:57.271
What?
- It's not fancy dress, you know.

11:57.360 --> 12:00.716
What?
- Lounge suits. It said so on the invite.

12:00.800 --> 12:03.314
Where?
- Small print at the bottom.

12:03.400 --> 12:07.234
I never read the small print. Oh, bloody
hell. I haven't brought a suit.

12:07.320 --> 12:09.629
Oh, half the men will be dressed like that.

12:09.720 --> 12:13.998
It might come in handy if we want
to put something on top of the cake.

12:18.480 --> 12:19.674
What?

12:20.720 --> 12:22.676
Excuse me.

12:23.960 --> 12:27.509
Oooh! I am not at all sure about this dress.

12:28.560 --> 12:31.757
Maybe I should change.
Rach, do you think I should change?

12:31.840 --> 12:33.831
If it'd make you feel better.

12:33.920 --> 12:36.832
Do you hate it?
- No, I don't.

12:36.920 --> 12:38.672
Oh! I'm going to change.

12:39.760 --> 12:41.716
She's more on edge than I am.

12:47.120 --> 12:49.236
She may have good reason to be.

12:51.280 --> 12:52.599
Listen.

12:53.640 --> 12:55.676
David's having an affair.

12:57.200 --> 13:01.352
We've already been through that one.
- Oh, my God, does she know?

13:03.720 --> 13:06.314
You're joking.
- No.

13:07.400 --> 13:09.595
Robert saw them.

13:09.680 --> 13:13.229
David was in a restaurant
with that Jessica woman.

13:13.320 --> 13:15.356
All lovey-dovey and that.

13:16.160 --> 13:18.628
Jessica?
- Yeah.

13:18.720 --> 13:20.631
Oh, my God.

13:20.720 --> 13:23.154
She thought he was up to something.

13:23.240 --> 13:26.198
I just told her she was being ridiculous.

13:26.280 --> 13:28.714
Shit! The car's here.

13:28.800 --> 13:29.915
Are you all right?

13:30.000 --> 13:31.228
Yeah.

13:31.320 --> 13:33.276
Nervous.

13:35.760 --> 13:37.352
Come on, mate. It's just nerves.

13:38.400 --> 13:40.595
It's not nerves. It's those bloody sausages.

13:40.680 --> 13:44.673
I had them as well.
- Yeah, well, you only had one.

13:44.760 --> 13:47.513
Besides, the abuse your body has taken
over the years...

13:47.600 --> 13:49.397
So, is the car here yet?
- No.

13:49.480 --> 13:53.268
Well, have you rung it? - I don't know
what firm it is. Jenny organised it.

13:53.360 --> 13:56.796
Jenny organised the girls' car.

13:56.880 --> 13:58.313
You were supposed to do ours.

13:58.400 --> 14:00.197
Are you sure?

14:00.280 --> 14:01.793
Right, I'll do the taxis.

14:02.840 --> 14:06.992
Oh, hey! I don't want a beaten-up old car.
I want to arrive in style.

14:07.080 --> 14:09.275
You know - limo, Cadillac?

14:09.360 --> 14:11.271
Taxi's fine by me.

14:11.360 --> 14:13.874
OK, I'll do the girls' transport.

14:13.960 --> 14:16.997
Best man can do the boys'.
All right, Pete?

14:17.080 --> 14:20.993
Do these things have a sell-by date?
- I don't know. Check the small print.

14:23.680 --> 14:26.592
Start phoning cab firms.

14:26.680 --> 14:29.797
Right. Do you still want a limo?
- I just want a lift!

14:29.880 --> 14:31.472
Where are you going?
- The loo.

14:38.760 --> 14:40.034
Oh, sorry.

14:41.080 --> 14:44.231
I don't know much about flowers,
but these are stupendous.

14:44.320 --> 14:46.311
David! I want a word with you.

14:46.400 --> 14:48.311
Rach, we've got to go.

14:48.400 --> 14:52.029
Are you still here? Come on!
- Don't worry. I'll be there ahead of you.

14:52.120 --> 14:56.033
Marsden.

14:56.120 --> 14:58.759
I've tried the local cab firms and...

14:58.840 --> 15:01.957
they can't do anything in under
half an hour.

15:02.040 --> 15:05.112
Well, haven't you got a car?
- No, and Rachel's took theirs.

15:05.200 --> 15:08.749
Well, no, I'm sorry.
The Merc's at the mechanic's.

15:08.840 --> 15:11.274
Well, German engineering for you.

15:11.360 --> 15:13.510
Yeah. How are you going to get there?

15:14.560 --> 15:16.790
Look, um...you swing by here

15:17.680 --> 15:21.150
and I'll keep trying the local firms.

15:21.240 --> 15:23.196
OK.

15:33.520 --> 15:35.715
Is everything all right?

15:35.800 --> 15:37.199
Well, the weather's holding.

15:37.280 --> 15:39.191
Adam's not here yet.

15:39.280 --> 15:40.349
Or the best man.

15:40.440 --> 15:42.032
Or my husband.

15:43.040 --> 15:45.713
Well, if you'd like me to give you away...

15:45.800 --> 15:48.837
Dad, without a groom
there's very little point, is there?

15:51.040 --> 15:54.635
They'll just be stuck in traffic.
- Unless he's having second thoughts!

15:54.720 --> 15:56.950
Either way, Rach, you should stay
out of sight.

15:57.040 --> 16:01.272
He shouldn't see you before the ceremony.
- Mum, hold these. Jen, come with me.

16:07.000 --> 16:10.788
Do you think we should tell Karen?
- Oh, God! I don't think I could.

16:10.880 --> 16:12.791
Jenny, she told you.

16:12.880 --> 16:14.791
Yes, she did.

16:14.880 --> 16:17.792
Ho-ly shite! Ho-ly shite!

16:17.880 --> 16:20.440
Oh, God!

16:26.360 --> 16:28.316
OK, David's here.

16:36.400 --> 16:38.356
Good luck, man.

16:39.640 --> 16:41.119
Time to get married.

16:41.200 --> 16:43.156
Yeah.

16:45.560 --> 16:46.675
Still no sign.

16:46.760 --> 16:49.638
Jenny and I are having a private word.

16:49.720 --> 16:52.439
Oh, my God. It's about my dress, isn't it?

16:52.520 --> 16:55.318
You what?
- Is it because it's see-through?

16:55.400 --> 16:57.868
No, it is not about your dress! Now, go on!

17:01.600 --> 17:04.672
Oh, God!
- Hey, do you girls fancy a brew?

17:21.200 --> 17:23.953
It's certainly stylish. What kept you?

17:24.040 --> 17:27.669
Best man tried to poison me,
then he took me hostage.

17:27.760 --> 17:30.513
Where is he?
- On his way, hopefully.

17:37.400 --> 17:39.356
<i>Rachel, you're on!</i>

17:40.640 --> 17:43.677
Hi, guys. Hey, John, look. Present for you.

17:43.760 --> 17:45.751
Thank you. Hello, everyone.

17:45.840 --> 17:47.956
Oh! Can you take that, please?

17:48.880 --> 17:51.110
All right, guys? Hi, how are you?

17:51.200 --> 17:53.156
Right, here we are, then.

17:53.240 --> 17:56.277
Wait, wait. I want you two
to go in ahead of us.

17:56.360 --> 17:59.193
We're supposed to follow you.
It's tradition, isn't it?

17:59.280 --> 18:01.430
So's... So's burning witches.

18:01.520 --> 18:04.512
So sod tradition and get up there.
- Come on!

18:07.080 --> 18:09.036
I'll just take this lot off.

18:10.200 --> 18:12.714
You're lucky we were able to wait.

18:12.800 --> 18:16.429
There's no-one after you.
We had a cancellation.

18:16.520 --> 18:18.511
Ah, just like a driving test.

18:18.600 --> 18:19.555
Why did they cancel?

18:19.640 --> 18:23.952
Oh, the divorce hadn't come through yet.
One of them was still married.

18:24.040 --> 18:26.395
Not as strange as you think, mate.

18:31.800 --> 18:36.157
Do you want to wait for your best man?
- Oh, yes... Oh, no. Let's go.

18:40.760 --> 18:42.751
Rachel, you look wonderful.

18:42.840 --> 18:46.071
Here, don't forget your bouquet.
- David, I...

18:46.160 --> 18:50.278
That's our cue. Are you ready?

18:59.560 --> 19:02.950
David, I've got to know.
Are you having an affair?

19:04.000 --> 19:07.151
Who told you that?
- God, David.

19:07.240 --> 19:08.958
Why didn't you just say no?

19:11.160 --> 19:12.798
No?

19:13.840 --> 19:15.876
Can you just give us a minute?

19:21.040 --> 19:22.996
David!

19:31.160 --> 19:34.709
Listen, I...I just made a dreadful mistake.

19:34.800 --> 19:38.952
I don't know what was happening to me.
I had a sort of brainstorm.

19:39.040 --> 19:41.474
This beautiful woman flattered me

19:41.560 --> 19:43.790
and I allowed it to turn my head.

19:43.880 --> 19:48.510
You and Karen are the only advert
for a good marriage that I know!

19:48.600 --> 19:52.275
It's terrific to find out on my wedding day
that it's a complete sham!

19:52.360 --> 19:57.229
It's not a sham! I adore Karen and the children.
I wouldn't do anything to hurt them.

19:58.840 --> 20:00.831
Look, it only happened once.

20:00.920 --> 20:03.718
When I came to my senses,
I put an end to it.

20:05.840 --> 20:07.273
I promise you.

20:07.360 --> 20:09.316
What's happening?

20:09.680 --> 20:12.399
I'll go and check.
- No, it's fine. It's her dress.

20:12.480 --> 20:15.677
The zip's gone, I...I think.
- At least it's not see-through.

20:15.760 --> 20:17.671
Where's the toilet?

20:17.760 --> 20:19.671
Through that door, second on the left.

20:19.760 --> 20:21.671
Great!

20:21.760 --> 20:23.671
