keeping secrets from each other?

24:53.760 --> 24:55.716
All right. Upstairs.

24:59.080 --> 25:01.799
Jessica? Well, you have to hand it to him.

25:02.640 --> 25:05.552
Adam!
- What? Er, oh, yeah.

25:05.640 --> 25:09.030
And Karen doesn't know? Holy shite!

25:09.120 --> 25:11.509
Sorry, there's somebody in here.

25:11.600 --> 25:13.511
It's Jen. Let us in.

25:13.600 --> 25:15.556
Unless you're having sex.

25:19.160 --> 25:21.071
Well? What did he say?

25:21.160 --> 25:22.718
There we go.

25:23.760 --> 25:27.673
Come on. You say good night.
I have to get you in the bath.

25:27.760 --> 25:29.990
I think we have to say good night.

25:30.080 --> 25:32.753
Come on, Joshie. Time for bed.
- OK, you go with Daddy.

25:32.840 --> 25:34.751
Where are Adam and Rachel?

25:34.840 --> 25:38.469
Probably gone to consummate the marriage.
- With Jenny?

25:39.520 --> 25:41.476
Night, darling.

25:41.920 --> 25:44.434
I just want to get back to my wedding.

25:44.520 --> 25:47.398
Are we going to tell her?
- Do we have to discuss this now?

25:47.480 --> 25:50.313
If it's over, Karen does not need to know.

25:50.400 --> 25:52.834
Karen does not need to know what?

25:52.920 --> 25:54.319
Lock the door.

25:54.400 --> 25:57.358
Turn that bloody camera off.
- I can't. It's cinema verite!

25:57.440 --> 25:58.668
Off!

26:02.160 --> 26:04.071
So...

26:04.160 --> 26:06.116
What gives?

26:07.160 --> 26:11.278
David's having an affair.
- Yeah, with Jessica. It's been going on for ages.

26:11.360 --> 26:13.920
You know?
- Of course. I rumbled him in Ireland.

26:14.000 --> 26:17.072
And you didn't say anything?
- If anything, I'm discreet!

26:17.160 --> 26:21.073
Honour among adulterers. Lovely!
- So now everyone knows. Except Karen.

26:21.160 --> 26:23.230
And that is how it should stay.

26:23.320 --> 26:25.436
No.
- Yes!

26:25.520 --> 26:27.670
I just want to get back to my wedding.

26:27.760 --> 26:30.479
I'm sorry. We've got to say something.

26:33.240 --> 26:35.196
Tell that one to Tim.

26:37.080 --> 26:40.038
Hi, darling.
- Now Pete's disappeared, as well.

26:40.120 --> 26:41.189
What?

26:41.280 --> 26:43.874
He's probably running
his best man's speech past them.

26:43.960 --> 26:45.916
Yeah. I hope you're right.

26:48.000 --> 26:50.594
<i>We're her friends. We have to interfere.</i>

26:50.680 --> 26:54.150
This is really none of our business.
- David has made it our business.

26:54.240 --> 26:56.959
Uh-uh. Your boyfriend has.
- He's my ex, thank you!

26:57.040 --> 26:59.713
I'm single, too, you know.
- Since when?

26:59.800 --> 27:02.234
Can we discuss this another time?

27:02.320 --> 27:03.719
Karen has got the right to know.

27:03.800 --> 27:08.954
It wasn't an affair. They only did it once.
- I suppose a blow job doesn't count, either.

27:10.320 --> 27:12.231
You are marrying him!

27:12.320 --> 27:14.993
Whatever the wrongs and rights,
it's over. Just let it lie.

27:15.080 --> 27:17.435
Am I the only one with any sense?

27:17.520 --> 27:19.317
Shh! Somebody's coming.

27:19.400 --> 27:21.072
<i>Won't be a minute.</i>

27:21.160 --> 27:23.071
Rachel, is that you?

27:23.160 --> 27:27.676
Yes, Mum.
- Rachel, I need to come in. Now.

27:27.760 --> 27:30.558
We won't be a minute - I won't be a minute.

27:38.920 --> 27:40.876
Well, it's all yours, Mum.

27:42.680 --> 27:45.035
There you are. Is anything wrong?

27:46.080 --> 27:49.516
No, everything's just hunky-dory.
- Interesting.

27:49.600 --> 27:52.319
I think we're about ready for the cake.

27:53.760 --> 27:56.069
Rachel. What's going on?

27:56.160 --> 27:58.071
David, it's my wedding day.

27:58.160 --> 28:01.675
If you don't mind,
I'd like to enjoy it for just one moment!

28:01.760 --> 28:05.036
Where's the loo, David?
- It's just upstairs.

28:09.600 --> 28:14.355
I've spent weeks trying to think
of the right thing to say about her.

28:14.440 --> 28:17.910
Had I been a great mathematician,
or physicist, say,

28:18.960 --> 28:24.080
I might have found the exact formula
that explains the wonder of Rachel.

28:24.160 --> 28:26.674
But I was rubbish at those subjects.

28:26.760 --> 28:29.069
Or if I'd been a star at languages,

28:29.160 --> 28:32.709
maybe I could have come up
with the words of passion

28:32.800 --> 28:35.951
that illustrate just what she does to me.

28:36.040 --> 28:39.350
But, ''Que hay en la bolsa?''
''What is in the shopping bag?''

28:40.560 --> 28:42.551
doesn't quite hit the mark.

28:42.640 --> 28:44.551
English was my forte.

28:44.640 --> 28:48.713
Even then, nothing I come up with
comes close to describing

28:48.800 --> 28:53.669
how I feel about the girl that took
my breath away the minute I met her.

28:57.280 --> 28:59.999
With Rachel, I can't even get the words
in the right order.

29:01.800 --> 29:03.950
So, in closing,

29:04.040 --> 29:07.953
I'd just like to thank you all for being here
to share this happy day with us.

29:09.000 --> 29:10.115
And to my wife...

29:19.440 --> 29:21.510
..I would say,

29:21.600 --> 29:23.591
Williams Rachel,

29:24.440 --> 29:26.396
you I love.

29:35.800 --> 29:37.711
OK, OK, OK.

29:37.800 --> 29:39.711
The cake!

29:51.640 --> 29:54.074
Are you nervous about your speech?

29:54.160 --> 29:57.197
No! Well, no more than at our wedding.

29:57.280 --> 29:59.191
Oh, my God!

29:59.280 --> 30:03.273
Just start with a good joke or something.
You'll be fine.

30:03.360 --> 30:05.476
Yeah, yeah, great. Good idea.

30:07.840 --> 30:10.877
Do you know any?
- Oh, shut up.

30:15.240 --> 30:18.038
Rachel, please, I need to talk to you.
- David!

30:19.080 --> 30:21.036
OK. In the hallway.

30:21.520 --> 30:24.637
Sorry I've been slow
sending them divorce papers back.

30:24.720 --> 30:26.358
I know you want to get on with it.

30:26.440 --> 30:30.353
Let's not talk about divorce today?
Yeah? - Yeah.

30:32.400 --> 30:34.470
Everyone knows, don't they?

30:35.120 --> 30:36.758
Everyone except Karen.

30:37.800 --> 30:39.756
Oh, God.

30:42.480 --> 30:44.357
I've destroyed my marriage.

30:45.400 --> 30:47.356
Oh, for God's sake, David.

30:47.720 --> 30:51.349
I'm sorry about you and whatshername.
Um... Emma.

30:51.440 --> 30:53.158
I thought it was going really well.

30:53.240 --> 30:56.596
Well, it was. But I had to finish it
this morning.

30:56.680 --> 30:58.875
It wasn't working.
She was way out of my league.

30:58.960 --> 31:00.871
Thanks very much.

31:00.960 --> 31:02.757
Oh, I didn't mean...

31:03.800 --> 31:05.916
You're not such a bad catch, Pete.

31:06.960 --> 31:10.316
OK, everybody, while they're
cutting the cake,

31:10.400 --> 31:12.755
I'd like to call upon the best man.

31:14.000 --> 31:15.956
Hold on. Where's Rachel?

31:17.880 --> 31:21.077
I don't think anyone's going to
say anything,

31:21.160 --> 31:23.355
although I can't be sure about Jenny.

31:24.520 --> 31:26.431
It doesn't matter.

31:26.520 --> 31:30.069
You all know...and I know that you know.

31:31.520 --> 31:34.671
Rach, come on. Pete's about to do
his speech.

31:35.720 --> 31:36.755
Are you all right?

31:37.960 --> 31:39.075
Karen?

31:39.160 --> 31:41.116
What?

31:43.880 --> 31:45.836
I want you to sit down.

31:52.160 --> 31:55.277
Excuse me.
Folks, can I have your attention, please?

31:55.360 --> 32:00.559
Most grooms thank their best man
for getting him to the church on time.

32:00.640 --> 32:03.996
Thanks to mine, I nearly didn't get there at all.
- Come here.

32:04.080 --> 32:07.595
So rest assured that whatever he says
about me is nothing

32:07.680 --> 32:09.989
compared to what
I was saying about him earlier.

32:10.080 --> 32:12.548
He is an idiot.

32:12.640 --> 32:14.551
But he's my idiot.

32:14.640 --> 32:17.837
Ladies and gentlemen, my best man,
the one, the only Pete Gifford!

32:26.680 --> 32:28.875
<i>Shit!</i>

32:30.320 --> 32:33.232
Listen to that! Heckled before
I've even started!

32:33.320 --> 32:37.677
I will not allow this to interfere
with Adam and Rachel's day.

32:40.720 --> 32:43.029
You don't want to discuss it now?
- Upstairs!

32:54.640 --> 32:58.792
Now, Adam thinks he knows
all there is to know about Rachel.

32:58.880 --> 33:01.348
And there's a great deal to know.

33:01.440 --> 33:05.479
I wasn't going to mention it,
but earlier, Adam said to me

33:05.600 --> 33:08.717
that I can say anything I like.
I'm delighted.

33:08.800 --> 33:11.633
You said what?
- He promised to be discreet.

33:11.800 --> 33:14.234
Now, for example, Adam was worried

33:14.320 --> 33:17.551
he might not be man enough for Rachel.

33:17.640 --> 33:20.598
Oh, my God, not the missing bollock!

33:21.640 --> 33:25.030
And I'm not referring
to just the one testicle he has remaining,

33:27.000 --> 33:31.232
but his apparent inability to satisfy
her sexually,

33:31.320 --> 33:33.550
ladies and gentlemen. Oh, yes.

33:33.640 --> 33:36.359
You see, the other week,
Adam caught Rachel upstairs...

33:36.440 --> 33:39.910
How shall I put this? Um...on the bed,

33:40.000 --> 33:41.956
amusing herself.

33:46.000 --> 33:48.798
I think you know what I mean. Ooh, yeah.

33:49.440 --> 33:52.432
Well, Adam, you'll be relieved
to know, mate,

33:52.520 --> 33:56.752
