34:03.680 --> 34:07.309
But my sources do tell me
that she's still not afraid

34:07.400 --> 34:10.391
to play with the one she loves
now and again.

34:10.480 --> 34:12.755
Regularly. Wa-hey!

34:12.840 --> 34:14.795
What on earth is he on about?

34:16.639 --> 34:19.279
David should have been my best man.

34:21.440 --> 34:24.112
How could you...

34:25.159 --> 34:27.036
..treat me with so little respect?

34:27.120 --> 34:30.829
Karen... - Has the last eight years
meant nothing to you?

34:30.920 --> 34:31.830
Of course they...

34:31.920 --> 34:35.879
You're prepared to throw it all away
on some sordid little affair!

34:36.920 --> 34:39.150
Oh, my God. She was in this house!

34:40.840 --> 34:43.559
Karen, It wasn't here...and it was
just the once.

34:43.639 --> 34:45.790
I don't care!

34:45.880 --> 34:48.678
I don't care about the details. It happened!

34:48.760 --> 34:50.670
You let it happen!

34:50.760 --> 34:52.716
That's all I need to know.

34:55.159 --> 34:59.597
Jesus! It is so unoriginal.

35:00.480 --> 35:04.109
Just like every other pathetic,
middle-aged man

35:04.200 --> 35:06.714
who regards his wife with contempt!

35:06.800 --> 35:10.315
I do not regard you with contempt!
- Well, I...do...you!

35:12.840 --> 35:16.958
So, yes. Adam Williams finally gets married.

35:17.040 --> 35:19.634
There's a first time for everything.

35:19.720 --> 35:22.188
But second time for Rachel.

35:22.280 --> 35:23.474
I bet you didn't know that.

35:23.560 --> 35:25.471
Oh, shit!

35:25.560 --> 35:28.916
Not that it lasted long. Well, it did,
actually.

35:29.000 --> 35:30.911
But not until the divorce.

35:31.000 --> 35:35.073
That was when Adam found out,
when they moved in together.

35:35.160 --> 35:38.436
Then husband No.1 moved in, as well.
There was three of them together.

35:38.520 --> 35:40.272
Oh, shit.

35:40.360 --> 35:42.271
It was like a French film.

35:42.360 --> 35:45.158
Still, you have to laugh, don't you?

35:50.920 --> 35:52.876
Apparently not.

35:54.560 --> 35:56.835
<i>No, Joshie. Joshie!</i>

35:56.920 --> 35:59.480
Mummy, we're pllaying hide and seek.

36:01.320 --> 36:03.276
Why's Daddy sad?

36:04.400 --> 36:08.313
He's not sad.
He's just hurt himself, but he's fine now.

36:08.400 --> 36:11.949
We go back to your room
and I count to ten again, yes?

36:12.040 --> 36:14.395
Sorry, I'll leave you on your own.

36:17.960 --> 36:21.669
It's hard to meet someone
you want to spend your life with.

36:21.760 --> 36:23.591
When you do, make sure you don't blow it.

36:24.960 --> 36:28.396
Because after that, no-one else comes close.

36:28.480 --> 36:30.835
And who wants second best, eh?

36:30.920 --> 36:34.469
Adam and Rachel
have got a better chance than most.

36:35.520 --> 36:42.039
They're clearly meant for each other. Besides,
they can learn from their friends' mistakes.

36:43.120 --> 36:45.714
And now, I'd like to ask you all

36:45.800 --> 36:48.360
to raise a glass to the happy couple,

36:49.600 --> 36:51.158
Adam and Rachel.

36:51.240 --> 36:53.390
<i>Adam and Rachel.</i>

36:56.680 --> 36:59.319
So...

36:59.400 --> 37:00.833
..I'd best pack a bag.

37:01.880 --> 37:04.394
Slip out before anyone notices

37:04.480 --> 37:06.436
and move into a hotel.

37:07.240 --> 37:09.151
No, you won't.

37:09.240 --> 37:12.471
I won't allow that woman to
destroy my family.

37:14.080 --> 37:16.548
I despise you for being so weak.

37:16.640 --> 37:19.313
But I don't want my children to suffer.

37:19.400 --> 37:21.675
You will sleep in the spare room.

37:26.280 --> 37:29.590
So, are you prepared
to give me another chance?

37:31.200 --> 37:33.509
We'll do what lots of people do, David.

37:34.560 --> 37:37.632
Smile in public.
Pretend we have a happy marriage.

37:38.680 --> 37:40.591
But we still can...

37:40.680 --> 37:43.638
...darling.

37:49.760 --> 37:52.035
Oooah. Thank God for that.

37:52.120 --> 37:53.269
Great speech.

37:53.360 --> 37:56.909
Thanks.
Hey, I just about got away with it, though.

37:57.000 --> 37:59.116
When you started on masturbation...

37:59.200 --> 38:02.078
We thought artificial insemination
wasn't too far behind.

38:02.160 --> 38:04.674
I knew there was something I forgot.

38:04.760 --> 38:07.479
Rachel. Can we have a word?

38:08.800 --> 38:10.756
Yep.

38:15.840 --> 38:17.796
Daddy.

38:19.880 --> 38:21.836
Hi. How are you?

38:24.320 --> 38:25.912
Hi. How's everybody's glasses?

38:26.000 --> 38:27.911
He's told her.

38:28.000 --> 38:29.911
Don't say anything, Jenny.

38:30.960 --> 38:34.999
There's plenty of salmon.
Help yourself. Can I top you up?

38:35.080 --> 38:36.991
And then you were divorced?

38:37.080 --> 38:38.069
I'm not now.

38:38.160 --> 38:40.071
Yes. Thank you. Later.

38:40.160 --> 38:43.152
But you know we don't approve of divorce.

38:43.240 --> 38:45.276
Yeah, I do. I just don't know why.

38:45.360 --> 38:48.238
Well, because marriage is for life.

38:48.320 --> 38:51.073
For better or worse?

38:51.160 --> 38:53.594
What kind of impression do
people have of you?

38:53.680 --> 38:55.318
What?

38:55.400 --> 38:57.470
What century are you lliving in?

38:57.560 --> 39:00.677
We don't do things
for appearances any more.

39:00.760 --> 39:03.513
Nobody cares that I married a black man.

39:03.600 --> 39:04.999
Black?

39:05.080 --> 39:08.914
Yes, black. You had a black son-in-law,
Mother. Is that a problem for you?

39:09.000 --> 39:10.752
What about the cultural differences?

39:10.840 --> 39:15.960
He was from Stoke. Have you got
something against people from Stoke?

39:16.040 --> 39:18.474
There's no need
to speak to your mother like that.

39:18.560 --> 39:20.994
There is absolutely every reason!

39:21.080 --> 39:24.152
It's about time we had some bloody honesty.

39:25.080 --> 39:27.150
I was married. I was pregnant.

39:27.240 --> 39:29.390
Didn't know who the father was.

39:29.480 --> 39:32.597
I had an abortion. Adam and I
can't have kids.

39:32.680 --> 39:37.595
Your younger daughter is a lesbian.
That's why she moved to Australia.

39:37.680 --> 39:41.514
Because she can't live the life
she wants to lead in this country.

39:44.600 --> 39:47.273
Right, I think that's about everything.

39:47.360 --> 39:49.271
Now it's your turn.

39:49.360 --> 39:51.476
Is Dad still hitting you, Mum?

39:52.600 --> 39:55.717
Your mum and I
have been married for 32 years.

39:55.800 --> 39:59.998
When you've been together as long,
then maybe you can lecture us.

40:02.000 --> 40:03.991
You know nothing, young lady.

40:05.040 --> 40:06.996
Well, she knows respect.

40:11.040 --> 40:14.430
Ruth, I won't stop in this house
a minute longer. Come on.

40:30.520 --> 40:32.715
They're nice, your parents.

40:37.760 --> 40:39.910
Are you all right?

40:40.000 --> 40:41.956
Yeah.

40:47.880 --> 40:51.589
Do you think I should have bitten my tongue?
- Ah! Do you wish you had?

40:52.880 --> 40:54.836
No, I don't.

40:56.120 --> 40:58.031
No.

40:58.120 --> 41:00.076
Thanks.

41:02.640 --> 41:06.315
Though I don't know
if you should have outed your sister.

41:06.400 --> 41:07.913
Bloody hell.

41:08.960 --> 41:11.394
Oh, my God. What time is it in Sydney?

41:11.480 --> 41:13.436
I thought she was in Alice.

41:14.520 --> 41:16.431
Alice?

41:16.520 --> 41:18.431
Ah, in Alice!

41:18.520 --> 41:20.476
Lesbian humour.

41:24.640 --> 41:26.596
Thanks.

41:32.840 --> 41:34.796
Oh, hi. Luce, it's me.

41:35.880 --> 41:37.791
Yeah, I'm married.

41:37.880 --> 41:39.552
Again.

41:40.600 --> 41:43.672
But listen, that's not why I'm ringing you.

41:48.760 --> 41:50.716
Fancy that.

41:52.400 --> 41:54.197
Yeah.

41:55.240 --> 41:57.435
What is it about weddings, anyway?

41:58.480 --> 42:00.391
Well, we did it after ours.

42:00.480 --> 42:02.436
I should bloody hope so.

42:05.080 --> 42:07.036
Going to stay for brekky?

42:08.720 --> 42:11.757
Well, I thought you had to pick
the nipper up.

42:12.800 --> 42:14.756
We'll do that after.

42:15.800 --> 42:17.677
We?

42:17.760 --> 42:19.716
If you want to.

42:20.880 --> 42:22.836
I know he'd like it.

42:24.240 --> 42:26.276
Yeah. He would, wouldn't he?

42:47.840 --> 42:50.798
Here you are.
- Thank you.

42:54.600 --> 42:57.717
I told Josh
you'd do some colouring with him.

42:57.800 --> 42:59.756
Oh... but...golf.

43:01.920 --> 43:06.277
Sorry. I'll ring the lads and scratch.
And do some colouring.

43:08.680 --> 43:12.275
How did you sleep?
- Fine, thanks. You?

43:12.360 --> 43:15.079
No. The mattress is lumpy.
I'll get a new one.

43:15.160 --> 43:17.628
You might want to decorate, as well.

43:53.160 --> 43:54.513
What?

43:55.560 --> 43:57.516
Nothing.

44:01.520 --> 44:02.669
What?

44:04.440 --> 44:07.432
I was just thinking how beautiful you are.

44:09.360 --> 44:11.316
How lucky I am.

44:13.240 --> 44:15.470
You don't mind that we didn't...

44:15.560 --> 44:17.949
consummate our marriage?

44:18.040 --> 44:19.871
Ohh...

44:19.960 --> 44:21.871
After all that booze,

44:21.960 --> 44:24.474
I don't think I could've managed it.

44:28.000 --> 44:31.959
Anyway, I wanted to save it until
we were feeling fresh.

44:32.280 --> 44:34.236
And how are you feeling now?

44:35.960 --> 44:37.916
Mmmm.

44:40.320 --> 44:42.276
I'm feeling fresh.

44:49.240 --> 44:50.559
Oh, give me one of those.

44:50.640 --> 44:53.757
I must warn you all that this is
just a rough cut.

44:53.840 --> 44:55.990
Oh, aye? Francis Ford Gifford!

44:56.080 --> 44:59.311
And the editing's dodgy
cos I did it from machine to machine.

44:59.400 --> 45:01.550
Oh, just show the bloody thing!

45:01.640 --> 45:04.154
Come on. Are you ready?

45:04.240 --> 45:06.913
Let love begin.

45:09.000 --> 45:10.274
Ah! How did you do that?

45:10.360 --> 45:14.148
That's little Adam's magnetic letters
on the fridge.

45:14.240 --> 45:16.151
<i>No expense spared.</i>

45:16.240 --> 45:18.196
<i>Ooh! Very good!</i>

45:22.960 --> 45:24.916
Who's that?

45:25.000 --> 45:26.956
I don't know her.

45:33.400 --> 45:35.311
It means a great deal to them.

45:36.360 --> 45:39.158
What were you doing?
- What's all this about?

45:40.560 --> 45:43.154
<i>I do solemnly declare.</i>

45:43.240 --> 45:46.676
I do...solemnly declare.

45:46.760 --> 45:48.193
God, those bloody workmen!

45:48.280 --> 45:50.191
They made a nice cup of tea.

45:50.280 --> 45:52.236
<i>They did.</i>

45:52.320 --> 45:53.639
Hey, does it actually count?

45:53.720 --> 45:55.870
Is it legal if you can't hear
the wedding vows?

45:55.960 --> 45:58.997
Um...you can lip-read them, though. Look.

46:03.560 --> 46:06.632
<i>Boo!
- Who took that, then?</i>

46:06.720 --> 46:08.631
I did.

46:08.720 --> 46:10.676
<i>Can't you tell?</i>

46:25.880 --> 46:27.472
<i>Oh, this is quality, Pete.</i>

46:29.280 --> 46:31.236
Real quality.

46:33.920 --> 46:36.832
Welcome to Chateau Marsden
for the arrival of the guests.

46:38.600 --> 46:40.670
What's that?
- Nothing.

46:40.760 --> 46:43.433
It looked like two naked men.

46:43.520 --> 46:45.875
It is.
- They're having a shower.

46:45.960 --> 46:49.430
I transferred the tape
onto one of Matthew's tapes.

46:49.520 --> 46:52.637
Your gay landlord?
- Ex-landlord.

46:52.720 --> 46:55.075
So our wedding is intercut with gay porn?

46:55.160 --> 46:57.674
<i>Don't get upset. He was devastated.</i>

46:57.760 --> 47:00.149
<i>That's one of his favourite films.</i>

47:01.200 --> 47:03.555
Now... OK, the cake.

47:06.000 --> 47:08.434
Not much of David and Karen in this.

47:08.520 --> 47:11.876
<i>Toast the happy couple, Adam and Rachel.</i>

47:11.960 --> 47:13.279
<i>Adam and Rachel.</i>

47:13.360 --> 47:15.112
Hey, where's my speech?

47:16.160 --> 47:18.310
Sorry. I had the record button on pause.

47:18.400 --> 47:20.356
Oh, yeah. Marvellous.

47:28.600 --> 47:30.556
That was nice.

47:33.000 --> 47:34.115
What, is that it?

47:34.200 --> 47:36.395
You told me to keep it short.

47:36.480 --> 47:38.471
Oh, you are a genius, you are.

